# SignalPilot Core Conventions

## Stack
- Python 3.12, Pydantic v2 (model_copy, Field factories), GitPython
- pytest with asyncio mode=AUTO; run via `/Users/aashu/.local/bin/python3.12 -m pytest`
- Tests live in `tests/unit/`; 242+ tests must stay green

## Project Layout
- `src/signalpilot/` — main package
- `src/signalpilot/collectors/` — data collectors (deploy, git, logs, metrics, etc.)
- `src/signalpilot/models.py` — all Pydantic models (single source of truth)
- `src/signalpilot/detect/` — regression/change-point detection
- `src/signalpilot/rca/` — root-cause analysis

## Key Models
- `DeployChange.git: Optional[GitChange]` — populated by `enrich_deploy_change`
- `GitChange` — repo, from_sha, to_sha, commits, suspect_commits, suspect_files
- `CommitInfo` — sha (12-char hex), author, message, files_changed, ts

## Git Collector (`collectors/git.py`)
- `resolve_commit_sha(image_tag, annotations, labels)` — SHA from annotations > labels > tag
- `diff_commits(repo_path, from_sha, to_sha)` — `None` from_sha → single HEAD commit
- `flag_suspect_commits(commits)` — source/infra/config files OR risky message keywords
- `build_git_change(...)` — full pipeline, degrades gracefully (returns None on error)
- `enrich_deploy_change(deploy_change, repo_path, ...)` — attaches GitChange to DeployChange
- Uses GitPython; clones remote URLs to tmpdir with depth=50

## Conventions
- Collectors degrade gracefully — return None / empty list, never raise to callers
- `_commit_to_info`: sha[:12], files from parent diff, limit 100 files
- SHA regex: `[0-9a-f]{7,40}` case-insensitive
- Pydantic: always use `model_copy(update={...})` (v2 API)
- No async in collectors/git.py — sync GitPython calls only
